      "y": 0,
      "width": 760,
      "height": 1160,
      "label": "Five Core Concepts",
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "1000000000000009",
      "type": "group",
      "x": -500,
      "y": 0,
      "width": 840,
      "height": 920,
      "label": "Three-Layer Architecture",
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "1000000000000018",
      "type": "group",
      "x": 400,
      "y": 0,
      "width": 740,
      "height": 920,
      "label": "System Behavior",
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "1000000000000001",
      "type": "file",
      "x": -1060,
      "y": -320,
      "width": 440,
      "height": 230,
      "file": "Sources/Clippings/Thin Harness, Fat Skills.md",
      "color": "3"
    },
    {
      "id": "1000000000000002",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -500,
      "y": -320,
      "width": 620,
      "height": 230,
      "text": "# Thin Harness, Fat Skills\n\nThe productivity jump is architectural, not model-side. The winning system keeps the harness small, moves repeatable judgment into markdown skills, and delegates reliable execution to deterministic tools.",
      "color": "3"
    },
    {
      "id": "1000000000000004",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1280,
      "y": 80,
      "width": 680,
      "height": 170,
      "text": "## 1. Skill Files\n\nReusable markdown procedures that teach **how** to do work. They behave like method calls: one procedure plus different parameters can become investigation, matching, enrichment, or review.",
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "1000000000000005",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1280,
      "y": 280,
      "width": 680,
      "height": 170,
      "text": "## 2. Harness\n\nThe program around the LLM: loop the model, read/write files, manage context, and enforce safety. The harness should stay thin and use fast, narrow tools instead of bloated tool catalogs.",
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "1000000000000006",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1280,
      "y": 480,
      "width": 680,
      "height": 170,
      "text": "## 3. Resolvers\n\nContext routing tables: when task type X appears, load document or skill Y. Descriptions, pointers, and lightweight rules replace giant always-loaded instruction files.",
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "1000000000000007",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1280,
      "y": 680,
      "width": 680,
      "height": 170,
      "text": "## 4. Latent vs Deterministic\n\nLatent space is for judgment, synthesis, pattern recognition, and ambiguity. Deterministic code is for trust: SQL, arithmetic, compiled code, assignment algorithms, and repeatable execution.",
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "1000000000000008",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1280,
      "y": 880,
      "width": 680,
      "height": 190,
      "text": "## 5. Diarization\n\nThe analyst step: read many documents, hold contradictions in mind, and produce one structured profile or brief. It turns raw retrieval into useful judgment.",
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "1000000000000010",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -460,
      "y": 90,
      "width": 760,
      "height": 160,
      "text": "## Top Layer: Fat Skills\n\nMarkdown procedures encode judgment, domain knowledge, process, examples, and evaluation rules. This is where most of the value lives and where model upgrades compound.",
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "1000000000000011",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -460,
      "y": 300,
      "width": 760,
      "height": 150,
      "text": "## Middle Layer: Thin CLI Harness\n\nJSON in, text out. Read-only by default. It manages the model loop, context, file access, tool calls, and safety without swallowing the system's knowledge.",
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "1000000000000012",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -460,
      "y": 500,
      "width": 760,
      "height": 150,
      "text": "## Bottom Layer: Application\n\nDeterministic capabilities such as QueryDB, ReadDoc, Search, Timeline, browser checks, API pulls, embeddings, and assignment algorithms provide reliable execution.",
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "1000000000000013",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -460,
      "y": 700,
      "width": 760,
      "height": 130,
      "text": "## Directional Rule\n\nPush intelligence upward into skills. Push execution downward into deterministic tooling. Keep the harness thin so context remains clean and latency stays low.",
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "1000000000000017",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 440,
      "y": 90,
      "width": 660,
      "height": 260,
      "text": "## YC Example\n\nFounder enrichment, event matching, and post-event improvement use the same pattern. Skills decide how to read and judge; deterministic tools fetch data, run searches, compute stats, and assign seats.",
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "1000000000000015",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 440,
      "y": 400,
      "width": 660,
      "height": 230,
      "text": "## Learning Loop\n\nRetrieve, read, diarize, count, synthesize. Then survey, investigate, diarize weak outcomes, extract rules, and write them back into the skill file. The skill rewrites the system's future behavior.",
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "1000000000000016",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 440,
      "y": 680,
      "width": 660,
      "height": 160,
      "text": "## Main Anti-Pattern\n\nA fat harness with thin skills: dozens of tools, slow MCP round-trips, REST endpoint wrappers, context bloat, higher latency, and more failure modes.",
      "color": "1"
    }
  ],
